				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">comegordas wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">hi everybody! i'm having some troubles whit the palette.<br /><br />i'm already able to fetch all the color bits, even the attribute table's ones. by assembling all the 4 bits i get an index to access the palette. first of all, i have a question about this diagram wich is in the wiki:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">43210<br />|||||<br />|||++- Pixel value from tile data<br />|++--- Palette number from attribute table or OAM<br />+----- Background/Sprite select</div><br /><br />what about bit #4? i think that stands for the background/sprite palette selection, but don't know where does it comes from.<br /><br /></div>
<br />
<br />I believe that diagram is supposed to show you another way of looking at the palette memory at $3F00-$3F1F.  See, the bits 4-0 form the low byte of the palette address, and %xxx00 is always interpreted as the background color 0 or transparency.  The background tiles are always rendered with %0xxxx entries, and the sprites with %1xxxx entries.  Bit 4 doesn't really come into play for the programmer except when referencing the palette by VRAM address.
<br />
<br />I hope this doesn't lead to any more confusion.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Be whatever the situation demands.</div>
